        <p>
        <h4>March 29, 2018 : Week 8</h4>
            Last week we had Joe West, CTO of BounceX meet us in class. 
            He spoke of 4 important things to know about DevOps and the t
            ools associated with it.</p> 
            <ul class="nested">
                <li>
                    Business is the thing: DevOps services are expensive 
                    and don't always save money. We must give thought to 
                    cost, business and purpose before resorting to the t
                    ools instead of using them just because they are cool.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Rightsize toolchain: many a times, our business 
                    may not need all of the tools. simple combination 
                    of EC2, CI/CD and a Db may suffice. hence, it is 
                    importnat to understand where the optimization is worth. 
                </li>
                <li>
                    Productivity is the best practice: We must try to 
                    automate things that are done repeatedly and take 
                    much of our time.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Document and rehearse: Documentation is essential to 
                    keep a record for purposes of handover or backtracking 
                    or rollbacks. Rehearsing critical events makes us better 
                    equiped at handling the real scenarios.
                </li>
            </ul>
            
