        <p>
        <h4>March 7, 2018 : Week 5</h4>
            I'd like to summarize the amazing session by 
            StackOverflow's Tom Limoncelli.
            Tom started off by telling us about what 
            misconceptions everyone has 
            about DevOps, how the term is often bound to 
            a few tools like Jenkins, 
            Ansible, etc. but in reality its much more 
            than that.<br>
            So here it is: DevOps is applying DevOps 
            priciples to simple software 
            engineering processes.<br>
            The DevOps principles are :<br>
            </p>
            <ul class="nested">
                <li>
                    3 ways: Process, Communication/Feedback, 
                    Innovation
                </li>
                <li>
                    small batches: Force Fail Frequently, 
                    frequency reduces risk.
                </li>
                <li>
                    MVP-Minimum Valuable Product: Deliver 
                    some value, small features 
                    sooner than delivering entire product in the end.
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
